                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;It should be much helpful if the answer (or the edit with the WARNING on top) would explain to whom is risky if using that header() script in php. The question here is about a foreign site where we have no control, and that only allows us to navigate and see it from a browser, while if we need to access the resources from our server instead it launches the CORS protection (to not let us make too much inquiries per second). Therefore, my question still stands, what dangers do we visitors have if using in OUR server that header() script ?? Did the editor confused the visitor (us) with the host?&lt;/span&gt;

