            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Well, I did in trouble shooting a system and the CORS error threw me off, that it was just the timeout that was too short, which resulted in a closed connection. After increasing the timeout, the system performed perfectly. So yes the timeout caused a No &apos;Access-Control-Allow-Origin&apos; error which got me into this thread in the first place. So this might be helpful to others having this thrown along with a 504.&lt;/span&gt;

